{"tid":1067049,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"ä¸­åœ‹å®˜æ–¹ï¼šèª“è¦æ¶ˆæ»…åŸºç£å®—æ•™","createTime":"2019-03-18T09:28:23.000Z","updateTime":"2019-03-18T09:45:07.000Z","uid":47714,"like":8,"dislike":2,"uniUserReply":11,"replies":[{"pid":"76b038d429b79728d19c5f19e1be6aa748857d74","tid":1067049,"uid":47714,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-03-18T09:28:23.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"https://www.christianheadlines.com/blog/chinese-official-vows-to-eliminate-christianity-in-china.html\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.christianheadlines.com%2Fblog%2Fchinese-official-vows-to-eliminate-christianity-in-china.html&d=%2FQX5ewQS1riptUQ52WFoKnza4IX%2BHJq2V8VgSm%2B5QfQ%3D&h=4faa3ea6\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.christianheadlines.com/blog/chinese-official-vows-to-eliminate-christianity-in-china.html</a><br />\n<br />\n A Chinese official says the country is vowing to eliminate Christianity in China, according to The Christian Post.<br />\n<br />\nXu Xiaohong, head of the National Committee of the Three-Self Patriotic Movement of the Protestant Churches in China, says there are &ldquo;problems&rdquo; with Christianity in the country, calling the religion an &ldquo;infiltration.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;[We] must recognize that Chinese churches are surnamed &lsquo;China,&rsquo; not &lsquo;the West&rsquo;,&rdquo; Xu told delegates to the Chinese People&rsquo;s Political Consultative Conference at the Great Hall of the People in Beijing.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;The actions by anti-China forces that attempt to affect our social stability or even subvert the regime of our country are doomed to fail,&rdquo; he added.<br />\n<br />\nHe said he is worried that Christianity is a &ldquo;western&rdquo; influence that isn&rsquo;t best for the country.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;Therefore, people often say: &quot;One more Christian, one less Chinese,&rdquo; Xu said, according to Xinhua News Agency.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;For individual black sheep who, under the banner of Christianity, participate in subverting national security, we firmly support the country to bring them to justice,&rdquo; he added.<br />\n<br />\nChina already has a &ldquo;sinicization campaign&rdquo; that works to bring religions under the country&rsquo;s official atheist&rsquo;s party control.<br />\n<br />\nPart of that campaign includes trying to make the country&rsquo;s religions more &ldquo;Chinese&rdquo; and even rewriting the New Testament with Buddhist and Confucian teaching.<br />\n<br />\nThe government must approve any Christian churches in China and religious activities are strictly monitored and regulated. Christians who do not adhere to the laws are sometimes arrested.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;Somehow, men and women of faith are viewed as a threat to the Chinese Communist Party,&rdquo; he said. &ldquo;It is clear that China&rsquo;s misguided and cruel policies in Xinjiang are creating resentment, hatred, division, poverty, and anger.&rdquo;"},{"pid":"20fe57817c45995caf8809ef777cefbc67fd72ad","tid":1067049,"uid":30633,"like":0,"dislike":1,"score":-1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-03-18T09:28:49.000Z","msg":"1984"},{"pid":"01b9d520b460ea29528a8c5b914fd911fcc3890e","tid":1067049,"uid":105678,"like":4,"dislike":2,"score":2,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-03-18T09:29:34.000Z","msg":"å•±å•¦ï¼Œå…¨çƒæœ€å¤§é»‘ç¤¾æœƒvsæœ€å¤§é‚ªæ•™<br />\n<br />\nç‹—å’¬ç‹—å•¦ï¼"},{"pid":"327e8fe576b6d892586b332159bb8a5dc911994a","tid":1067049,"uid":130695,"like":2,"dislike":0,"score":2,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-03-18T09:29:50.000Z","msg":"å…¨ä¸–ç•Œæœ€å¤§é»‘ç¤¾æœƒåŒé‚ªæ•™å’ªå…±ç”¢é»¨å›‰<br />\næœ‰å…¶ä»–å®—æ•™ä½¢ä»²é»ä¸€è¨€å ‚"},{"pid":"e9460236f7e3a0a49cea3df91d0f1c3cdb0486b4","tid":1067049,"uid":77196,"like":0,"dislike":1,"score":-1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-03-18T09:29:54.000Z","msg":"<strong><span style=\"color: red;\">people often say: &quot;One more Christian, one less Chinese,&rdquo;</span></strong><br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"/assets/faces/l